handist.collections.dist

Class DistMultiMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.dist.DistMap<K,List<V>>
      • handist.collections.dist.DistMultiMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of the key used in the DistMultiMap
    V - type of the elements contained in the lists to which the keys map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace, DistributedCollection<List<V>,DistMap<K,List<V>>>, KeyRelocatable<K>, Serializable, Map<K,List<V>>

    public class DistMultiMap<K,V>
extends DistMap<K,List<V>>
    A Map data structure spread over the multiple places. This class allows multiple values for one key, those values being stored in a list.

      • writeReplace

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place
